FBIS4-35267 "drnes104_n_94002" FBIS-NES-94-104 Daily Report 28 May 1994 LEBANON Government Pushes UN Censure of Israel Government Pushes UN Censure of Israel Ministry Summons UNSC Ambassadors NC2805133594 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1300 GMT 28 May 94 NC2805133594 Beirut Radio Lebanon Arabic BFN [Text] Foreign Ministry Secretary General Zafir al-Hasan today summoned the ambassadors of the United States, Russia, France, Britain, and China for consultations on Lebanon's call for a UN Security Council [UNSC] meeting to discuss Israel's kidnapping of al-Hajj Mustafa al-Dirani. Al-Hasan said Lebanon's decision to request a Security Council meeting will not await a response by the five big powers. He explained that Lebanon's Permanent Representative to the UN Khalil Makkawi has been instructed to call for a meeting without specifying a date for it. After the meeting, Russian Ambassador Gennadiy Ilichev said he will convey Lebanon's request to his government for a decision. U.S. Ambassador Mark Hambley denied that he knows anything about U.S efforts to discourage Lebanon from calling for a UN Security Council meeting.
